{
  "stem": "17526.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Whatever non-Jewish people lived in Bendin, this was their church.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "The week after the Germans marched in, they encircled the entire area of the synagogue and they had bombed and burned and have shot everybody who tried to escape.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "This was an inferno a week after they marched in.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Everybody naturally went into hiding.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "We, living not too far from there, we could peek out and see flames engulfing, shooting up to the heavens for an entire day and night.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "This happened on a weekend.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "We didn't realize to what extent this-- this-- this tragic thing took place, we didn't understand.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "But on a Sunday morning, I couldn't be hidden any longer, I was too restless.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And I snuck out on the street and as we snuck out-- with a few other youngsters, naturally-- but as the fire subsided, we wanted to see what has happened.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "We knew something terrible happened.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And we walked out and we walked and we saw nothing but burned ruins, and we saw burned people.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And immediately a committee organized, we walked around with these burlap sacks and we up and the charred bodies, hands and parts of bodies, and hauled them away to a cemetery to give them a decent burial.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And then as days went on, we realized how many people are missing.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "A whole city, practically a whole little city within a city, all these poor people were shot as they tried to escape.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "Now, later on it came out that some people escaped into the church and a priest, whoever was in charge, did hide some people and they were saved that night.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "But hundreds-- literally hundreds-- of people were shot within the fires.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And this was just like a-- like a foreplay as to what is going to happen.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
